#Text=The Los Angeles Clippers defeated the Los Angeles Lakers , 108 - 92 , in Thursday 's season opener at Staples Center .
#Text=Strong frontcourt play helped push the Clippers to an easy win from the game 's early minutes , as Blake Griffin helped the team to a 70 run within the first six minutes .
#Text=Griffin was able to dominate from all over the floor , scoring a game - high 29 points including three three - pointers .
#Text=The Clippers ended up delivering punishing big man play throughout the game , as All-NBA center DeAndre Jordan tallied a whopping 24 rebounds in only 31 minutes of play .
#Text=The new - look Clippers ( 10 ) enjoyed an ideal start to their season , as the team appeared to fire on all cylinders on both sides of the ball .
#Text=Though the team lost superstar point guard Chris Paul to Houston over the offseason , LA still relied heavily on star power in Thursday 's win .
#Text=Griffin not only scored a game - high 29 points , but delivered a double - double with 12 rebounds .
#Text=Jordan , meanwhile , knocked down all four of his free - throw attempts , not allowing his weakness to be exploited as he dominated the boards .
#Text=The game also saw the debut of a number of new faces for the Clippers .
#Text=European rookie point guard Milos Teodosic got the start , logging 21 minutes of play and dishing out six assists .
#Text=Teodosic looked more aggressive as the game progressed , attacking the lane and relying on kick - out passes more heavily in the second half .
#Text=Newly acquired sixth man Lou Williams , meanwhile , enjoyed a 12 - point outing as he found a groove with the retooled Clippers second unit .
#Text=For the Lakers ( 0 - 1 ) , Thursday 's season debut marked the first appearance by highly - touted rookie point guard Lonzo Ball .
#Text=The debut did not go as planned , with Ball scoring only three points and shooting just 1 - of - 6 .
#Text=Ball struggled with a tough matchup against First Team All-Defense point guard Patrick Beverly , who played aggressive and physical defense on the rookie all night .
#Text=Still , Ball was able to contribute , as he pulled down nine rebounds and made a number of sharp outlet passes .
#Text=The more impressive Lakers debut came from veteran center Brook Lopez , who led the team with 20 points .
#Text=Lopez found a scoring groove in the second half and played effectively alongside ultra - athletic power forward Larry Nance Jr. , who had a 14 - point , 12 - rebound double - double .
#Text=The Lakers will host the Suns on Friday , while the Clippers will see them on Saturday .
